{"type":"text","timestamp":1782925782251,"sessionID":"ses_0e161ba06ffe4N4jFh0zF4Zwuf","part":{"id":"prt_f1ea8621e001f1Rv4tMDR7Fq3K","messageID":"msg_f1ea8483800101V3M7PgX4m6sY","sessionID":"ses_0e161ba06ffe4N4jFh0zF4Zwuf","type":"text","text":"All three phases complete. Artifacts written to the lineage directory:\n\n- **phase_init**: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, findings-registry.json\n- **phase_main_loop** (2 iterations, maxIterations reached): iteration-001.md (Q1+Q2: SDK session-state capabilities + mechanical loop-like definition), iteration-002.md (Q3+Q4: dispatch path grounding + phase 012 evidence + 2 concrete design options)\n- **phase_synthesis**: research.md (full report with 3 design options and trade-offs), convergence-report.md\n\n**Key research outputs:**\n- Q1 answered: SDK exposes `sessionID` per-call; in-process `Map` (3 plugins) and external file (mk-goal.js) both proven patterns\n- Q2 answered: loop-like = same loop-executor (prompt-parsed) dispatched ≥3 per session; `subagent_type` always `\"general\"` so cannot discriminate\n- Q3 answered: \"exactly one bounded hand-off\" stated in 4 documents; guard needs iteration-state heuristic to distinguish command-driven iterations from orchestrate re-dispatches\n- Q4 answered: GPT-5.5 inconsistently enforced Command-only (refused deep-research, allowed deep-review)\n- **Option A**: in-process counter (~40 lines, MEDIUM FP risk)\n- **Option B**: external state + iteration-aware counting (~80 lines, LOW FP risk) — recommended\n- **Option C**: telemetry-first rollout (supplementary)\n\nFANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:glm-max","time":{"start":1782925779486,"end":1782925782250}}}
